I prefer to xray just to show and highlight what's actually there, versus 'fakerays' or people that do a mix.

Here's a screenshot of my layers:
-Some sharpening on the base image
-Special sharpening on the xray region to try and bring out important details
-Levels to bring out what's under the clothes
-Color layers to reduce color noise, if it's more uniform it's easier to make smoother adjustments but I don't always do this if i'm going quickly
-Some noise reduction to get rid of artifacts, partial masking that out because it softens the image so you don't want to too smooth or lose too much detail
-Some brushing with the skintone to shift the clothes to be closer to the skin color and enhance the xray effect
